Last Broadcast Date: Wed 15 Feb 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Extraordinary personal stories from around the world: today, Matthew Bannister talks to Mohammad Jawad, a plastic surgeon rebuilding the faces of acid victims in Pakistan. Mohammad's work is the subject of a documentary called "Saving Face" which has been nominated for an Oscar. And we hear from the Chinese Mongolian group Anda Union and their filmmaker manager Tim Pearce. "Saving Face" will be aired in the UK on Channel 4 in early April. Show less